This paper deals with recommendation algorithms and their evaluation in a real-world application, specifically in the context of a travel website. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Information Retrieval (cs.IR) sub-category, which deals with the retrieval of information from large datasets. Additionally, the paper uses multi-criteria rating data to build ranking models, which suggests that it may also belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-category, which deals with the development of algorithms that can learn from data. The paper also focuses on user engagement, which suggests that it may belong to the Human-Computer Interaction (cs.HC) sub-category, which deals with the design and evaluation of interactive systems. Finally, the paper may also belong to the Cybersecurity (cs.CY) sub-category, as it deals with the security and privacy of user data, and the Social and Information Networks (cs.SI) sub-category, as it deals with the analysis of social networks and user behavior.
